using UnityEngine;

public class RigidbodyError : MonoBehaviour
{
    public Rigidbody2D rb;

    void Update()
    {
        // Modifying transform on a physics object!
        transform.position += Vector3.right * 5f * Time.deltaTime;

        // This will cause physics issues!
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
Modifying `transform.position` on a Rigidbody bypasses the physics system.

**The fix:**
```csharp
void FixedUpdate()
{
    // Use Rigidbody for physics objects
    rb.MovePosition(rb.position + Vector2.right * 5f * Time.fixedDeltaTime);
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Don't modify Transform on physics objects. Use Rigidbody methods instead."
